Changing the SID property from type `System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier` to `System.String` in the bound object stops the exception and essentially fixes the problem, but this is still a serious bug and happens when binding other objects as well (link at top).

For example,
```
[BindProperty(Name = "the")]
public class IndexModel : PageModel
{
    public string FirstName { get; set; } = "John";
}
```
The `FirstName` property is bound to a `firstname` field. Neither `the` nor `the.firstname` fields will bind to this property.

The `Name` property *does* work fine when the `[BindProperty]` (or `[Bind]` &hellip;) attribute is associated with a page model property. The problem is specific to specifying the `Name` on the class.
